HEADWORD: Parasita
<hw>Par`a*si"ta</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧r`⟦adot⟧*s⟦imac⟧"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>An artificial group formerly made for parasitic insects, as lice,
ticks, mites, etc.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A division of copepod
Crustacea, having a sucking mouth, as the lerneans. They are mostly
parasites on fishes. Called also
<altname><ord>Siphonostomata</ord></altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

